                  <origin>
                     <origPlace cert="high" ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7002473"
                        >Istanbul</origPlace> completed <q xml:lang="en">by order of the
                        treasury</q> (<q xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc"><hi rend="italic">bi-rasm-i
                           khizānah</hi></q>) of <persName type="standard" role="pat dte"
                        key="person_44058182" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/44058182">Sultan Selim II
                        (1566–1574)</persName>, as per the dedication on folio <locus from="4a"
                        to="4a">4a</locus>. </origin>
                  <provenance><p>Subsequently acquired by French orientalist <persName role="fmo"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/51695910" key="person_51695910">Antoine-Isaac
                           Silvestre de Sacy, (1758–1838)</persName>, as per notations on folios
                           <locus from="1a" to="1a">1a</locus> and <locus from="193a" to="193a"
                           >193a</locus> which correspond to his <date calendar="#Gregorian"
                           when="1843">1843</date> library sale catalogue, no. 325.
                     </p></provenance>
                  <provenance><p>Purchased in <placeName
                           ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7008038">Paris</placeName> at the de
                        Sacy sale by scholar <persName type="standard" role="fmo"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/20108923/" key="person_20108923">Nathaniel
                           Bland (1803–1865)</persName>, after whose death <placeName
